The paper proposes a novel algorithm for Hierarchical Reinforcement Learning, which is a subfield of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a new policy gradient and baseline, which are common topics in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method is designed to efficiently train all levels of the hierarchy simultaneously, which is a common problem in Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of time-abstractions, which is a technique commonly used in Computer Vision (cs.CV) for video analysis.
